    <p><strong>Sugarcane juice machine prices in India in 2026 range from ₹15,000 for a basic manual hand-operated crusher to over ₹1,50,000 for a fully automatic sugarcane juice extraction system with built-in filtering.</strong> Whether you're starting a roadside sugarcane juice stall, adding fresh juice to your restaurant menu, or scaling up a juice bar franchise, understanding the sugarcane machine price landscape is essential to making a smart investment. This comprehensive buyer's guide covers every type, brand, price point, and business consideration you need to know before purchasing a sugarcane juice machine in India.</p>

    <p>Sugarcane juice (ganne ka ras) is one of India's most popular street beverages, especially during the summer months from March to September. The business opportunity is enormous — a single stall can generate ₹3,000–₹8,000 in daily revenue during peak season with margins exceeding 60%. But everything starts with choosing the right machine at the right price.</p>

