    <h2>Types of Sugarcane Juice Machines in India</h2>
    <p>Sugarcane juice machines available in India fall into three broad categories. Each type has its own advantages, limitations, and ideal use case. Let's break them down in detail.</p>

    <h3>1. Manual Hand-Operated Sugarcane Crusher</h3>
    <p>The manual sugarcane crusher is the most traditional and affordable option. It uses a hand crank mechanism to rotate heavy rollers (typically 2 or 3 rollers) that crush the sugarcane stalks and extract juice. The operator feeds cane into the top, turns the handle, and juice flows out from the bottom into a collection tray.</p>

    <p><strong>Key specifications:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Roller material:</strong> Cast iron (basic) or stainless steel (SS 304 — recommended)</li>
      <li><strong>Number of rollers:</strong> 2 rollers (basic) or 3 rollers (better extraction)</li>
      <li><strong>Extraction efficiency:</strong> 55–65% juice extraction from cane weight</li>
      <li><strong>Output:</strong> 40–80 glasses per hour (depends on operator strength and speed)</li>
      <li><strong>Weight:</strong> 25–50 kg depending on build</li>
      <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Minimal — periodic oiling of gears and rollers</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>No electricity needed — works anywhere, including remote locations and mobile carts</li>
      <li>Lowest upfront cost (₹15,000 – ₹25,000)</li>
      <li>Very low maintenance — no motor, no electrical components to fail</li>
      <li>Portable and lightweight — easy to move between locations</li>
      <li>Customers often perceive hand-pressed juice as more "natural" and fresh</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Physically demanding — operators tire quickly in hot weather</li>
      <li>Lower extraction rate means more wastage of cane</li>
      <li>Output is limited and operator-dependent</li>
      <li>Not suitable for high-volume locations (markets, malls, busy intersections)</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Budget-conscious entrepreneurs, village/rural stalls, mobile carts, very small operations serving fewer than 100 glasses per day.</p>

    <h3>2. Electric Motorized Sugarcane Juice Machine</h3>
    <p>The electric sugarcane juice machine replaces manual effort with a motor-driven roller system. The operator feeds sugarcane stalks into the rollers, and the motor does the heavy work of crushing. These are the most popular choice for commercial sugarcane juice stalls across India, from roadside setups to mall kiosks.</p>

    <p><strong>Key specifications:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Motor power:</strong> 0.5 HP to 3 HP (most common: 1 HP and 1.5 HP)</li>
      <li><strong>Roller material:</strong> Stainless steel 304 grade (food-safe standard)</li>
      <li><strong>Number of rollers:</strong> 3 rollers (standard) or 4 rollers (premium — higher extraction)</li>
      <li><strong>Extraction efficiency:</strong> 70–85% juice extraction</li>
      <li><strong>Output:</strong> 80–250 glasses per hour depending on motor power</li>
      <li><strong>Power requirement:</strong> Single-phase (up to 1.5 HP) or three-phase (2 HP and above)</li>
      <li><strong>Weight:</strong> 50–120 kg</li>
    </ul>

