      <li><strong>Standard commercial stall (₹30,000–₹50,000):</strong> A 1 HP or 1.5 HP electric machine from Kalsi or Tiger is the sweet spot. This handles 150–220 glasses per hour — enough for even busy locations. Insist on full SS 304 construction.</li>
      <li><strong>High-volume juice bar or restaurant (₹50,000–₹1,00,000):</strong> Invest in a 2–3 HP automatic machine with built-in filtering. The higher extraction rate and clean juice output justify the premium price, especially in a branded or restaurant setting.</li>
      <li><strong>Industrial / factory scale (₹1,00,000+):</strong> For large-scale sugarcane juice production (packaged juice, syrup manufacturing), you need industrial-grade automatic machines. Consult directly with manufacturers for custom specifications.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Whatever machine you choose, remember that the right sugarcane machine price is not the lowest price — it's the price that gives you the best value over the machine's lifetime, considering output, durability, maintenance costs, and hygiene compliance. If you're investing in other food business equipment alongside your juice machine, our <a href="/blog/commercial-kitchen-equipment-guide">commercial kitchen equipment guide</a> covers everything from ovens to refrigeration to help you set up right.</p>

